  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Oxygen desaturation (SO2 &lt; 88-90%) during walking is a common clinical feature of Chronic
      Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) patients. By a predicted analysis our study is aimed to
      evaluate anthropometric and functional characteristics of COPD patients correlated with
      oxygen desaturation during Six-minute walking test (6MWT).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
